column5: Well this cold snap is maken some good ice on the River now took a ride down river last night on the ATV to find 4 to 6 inches in pretty much all the river ...go get them Walleye guys ...i will be out in search of |Walleye later today will report this eve ...Fishmaster
I'm guessing a little to cold for a test run with the new boat Albert.
Ice conditions were good today.some good solid ice,4-6in by steves place.Very windy and cold out there,bring your heaters and huts.Im glad I did.
I'm in Fonthill, thinking of the Grand later this week when the temp & winds are a little more favourable.  Is the ice ok for ATVs?  Thanx for your help
speaking of minnows, where did you get yours?
